## Headlines Pipeline Architecture
- **rex-notes.md** (`/Users/rex/.openclaw/workspace/rex-notes.md`) — Rex's canonical market intelligence file
  - Rex maintains this; never auto-overwritten by Kelly's raw files
  - Format: `## YYYY-MM-DD — [headline]` → `### SNAPSHOT | MACRO | BITCOIN | ETHEREUM | INSTITUTIONAL | POLICY | KEY_NARRATIVE | CONTENT_ANGLES`
  - Newest entry at top; one entry per day
  - When Kelly sends market-notes.md → Rex reads it → normalizes into rex-notes.md format → prepends new entry
  - ZERO fabrication — only data explicitly in Kelly's notes
- **market-notes.md** — Kelly's raw daily notes; saved to `market-reports/market-notes.md` (replaced daily)
- **Convex sync**: API reads rex-notes.md → parses `## YYYY-MM-DD` sections → stores each with `dataTimestamp` (midnight UTC)
- **Headlines "Read full analysis"**: reads from Convex `knowledgeBase` → `extractRelevantContext()` matches headline date + category to rex-notes.md sections

