## X Feed Infrastructure Build Plan (Planned for 2026-03-06)

### Goal
Shared RSS feed infrastructure for the full agent network — pulling X posts + other sources (YouTube, Reddit, newsletters) into the headlines pipeline.

### Key Decisions
- **X API Basic ($100/mo)** — official route, no ToS risk, no auth cookie maintenance, reliable
- **Railway.app** for hosting the RSS adapter service — Kelly already has Pro, zero extra hosting cost
- No throwaway account needed — Bearer Token auth reads public tweets without any X account login
- Build session uses **Claude Sonnet 4.6**

### Kelly's Pre-Build Checklist
- [x] Railway Pro already subscribed — hosting covered
- [x] Going X API route ($100/mo) — decided 2026-03-06
- [ ] Create a throwaway Gmail (non-Hit Network, non-org email)
- [ ] Create a fresh X account on that Gmail — this is the developer account owner, not used for anything else
- [ ] Sign up for X API Basic at developer.twitter.com/en/portal using that X account ($100/mo)
- [ ] Create a new Project + App in the developer portal
- [ ] Generate Bearer Token (under "Keys and Tokens" in the app settings)
- [ ] Share Bearer Token with Rex securely (set as Railway env var — never hardcoded)
- [ ] Provide list of X accounts to monitor (crypto journalists, analysts, influencers)

### Build Phases
1. Build a small Node.js RSS adapter service on Railway:
   - Takes a configured list of X account handles
   - Hits X API v2 `/2/users/:id/tweets` with Bearer Token
   - Converts tweet data to RSS XML format
   - Exposes `GET /rss` endpoint → plugs directly into existing headlines pipeline
   - 15-min in-memory cache to stay within API rate limits
2. Deploy to Railway — set Bearer Token as env var
3. Test service is returning RSS feed with real tweets
4. Add Railway service URL to `RSS_SOURCES` in `convex/headlines.ts`
5. Tune relevance scoring for social post content (shorter, different format than news articles)
6. Team access — document endpoint, update Writer/Monitor/Analyst skills

### Architecture
```
X API v2 (Bearer Token — official, no account risk)
    ↓
RSS Adapter Service (Railway — always on)
    ↓ RSS feed endpoint
Rex → Mission Control headlines pipeline
Writer → content ideation
Monitor → breaking news alerts
Analyst → macro account tracking
```

### Cost
- Railway: $0 (already on Pro)
- X API Basic: $100/mo
- Total new spend: $100/mo

